pageContext.claim: “But Ukraine was great, we call them up. Do you mind if we release the conversation? No, we don't. Why? I said don't worry about it, just we're going to release it.”
pageContext.analysis: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky has said he thought only Trump's remarks would be released and said, "I personally think that sometimes such calls between presidents of independent countries should not be published."
